# Paperclip — Operations Playbook (gitignored)

> **Canonical source for the Paperclip orchestrator in your project.** Copy
> in this skill's templates; replace placeholders to match YOUR setup.
>
> **Audience:** Pilot + the architect orchestrator session.

---

## 1. Mental model

Paperclip is a **headless dispatcher of Claude Code** running on a droplet
with embedded Postgres + web dashboard. It schedules heartbeats, maintains
an Issue queue (Kanban), executes `claude --dangerously-skip-permissions`
as a subprocess in the configured `cwd`, passing the Issue body as input.

**Adopted topology:**

```
+----------+   architect   +-----------+    +-------------------+
|  Pilot   |---------------|           |--->|   N x dev-primary |
|  + arch  | decompose T-  | Paperclip |    |  Sonnet-class     |
| session  | file + dispatch|  API     |    |  worktree-per-issue|
+----------+ via curl       |           |    +---------+---------+
                            |           |              |
                            |           |              v
                            |           |    +---------+---------+
                            |           |--->|   1 x reviewer    |
                            |           |    |  Opus-class OAuth |
                            |           |    |  (Routine */10min)|
                            +-----------+    +-------------------+
```

**Architect = orchestrator session** (decomposes features, writes T-files, dispatches waves, has authority over always-human paths).
**Paperclip = scheduler** (executes Sonnet/Opus on droplet with controlled cadence).
**Pilot = final reviewer** (only reviews `feat/<slug> -> dev` PRs).

