## 3. Agent topology

### dev-primary (N replicas, recommend 3)

```json
{
  "name": "dev-primary-1",  // or -2, -3
  "adapterType": "claude_local",
  "adapterConfig": {
    "command": "claude",
    "extraArgs": ["--dangerously-skip-permissions"],
    "env": {
      "CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN_FILE": "/home/paperclip/.claude/auth.json"
    },
    "cwd": "/home/paperclip/repos/<your-repo>",
    "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
    "budgetMonthlyCents": 0
  },
  "schedule": {"enabled": false}  // turned ON per wave, NOT continuous
}
```

**Why schedule=false default?** A1 anti-pattern of the portable guide: identical replicas with identical config don't parallelize — first to heartbeat claims everything. Mitigation: schedule OFF + explicit `assigneeAgentId` when dispatching each wave. Pilot dispatches controlled cadence (wave of 3 parallel, wait for close, next wave).

**During the wave:** `PATCH /api/agents/<id> {"schedule":{"enabled":true,"intervalSec":120}}` on the 3 dev-primary.
**Post-wave:** `PATCH /api/agents/<id> {"schedule":{"enabled":false}}`.

### reviewer (1 replica)

```json
{
  "name": "reviewer",
  "adapterType": "claude_local",
  "adapterConfig": {
    "command": "claude",
    "extraArgs": ["--dangerously-skip-permissions"],
    "env": {"CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN_FILE": "/home/paperclip/.claude/auth.json"},
    "cwd": "/home/paperclip/repos/<your-repo>",
    "model": "claude-opus-4-7",
    "budgetMonthlyCents": 0
  },
  "schedule": {"enabled": false}
}
```

**Trigger:** Routine `review-pending-prs` (cron `*/10 * * * *`) creates an Issue assigned to the reviewer every time there's an open `task/* -> feat/*` PR without label `review-done`. Reviewer discovers PRs by scanning `gh pr list` at run start (instructed in `AGENTS-reviewer.md`).

### Shared Anthropic quota

OAuth token at `/home/paperclip/.claude/auth.json` may be **shared with other projects** running Paperclip on the same droplet. Windows:
- Sonnet (4.6): rolling 5h
- Opus (4.7): rolling 7d

**Mitigation:** Pilot **does not operate two projects simultaneously**. Architect monitors `lastHeartbeatAt` before each wave and checks `claude /usage` if uncertain.

