## 4. Branching strategy — 4 levels

```
main <--- dev <--- feat/<feature-slug> <--- task/<feature-slug>/<task-slug>
```

| Level | Created by | Off | Lifetime | PR target |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `main` | Pilot | — | permanent | release tag |
| `dev` | one time | `main` | permanent | only `main` (Pilot decides) |
| `feat/<slug>` | architect (orchestrator) when decomposing Paperclip feature | `dev` | until feature done | `dev` |
| `task/<feat-slug>/<task-slug>` | dev-primary when picking up Issue | `feat/<slug>` | until task done | `feat/<slug>` |

**Pilot reviews only `feat -> dev` PRs.** PRs `task -> feat` auto-merge with strong gate.

**Convention:** `<task-slug>` equals the T-file slug (without the `T<N>-` prefix). E.g. `T1-cosmos-card.md` -> branch `task/<your-feat-slug>/T1-cosmos-card`.

