## 5. Auto-merge gate (`task -> feat`)

Workflow `.github/workflows/auto-merge.yml` validates 4 checks before squash-merging:

1. **Fast-lane CI green** — your fast-lane workflow ran and passed (lint + typecheck + unit subset paths-filtered, ~3-4min).
2. **No always-human path touched** — script `scripts/check-always-human.sh` returns OK. **Customize the patterns in that script** for your project.
3. **Reviewer agent approved** — script `scripts/check-reviewer-approval.sh` does `gh pr view --json reviews,comments` and looks for the reviewer agent comment with APPROVE.
4. **Coverage >= 90% on diff** — fast-lane CI emits coverage artifact. Workflow reads it. **Skip coverage if diff is only `*.md` or new `*.test.*`** (no new code to test).

**If all pass:** `gh pr merge --squash --delete-branch`.
**If any fails:** comment on PR explaining + remove label `auto-merge`. Architect or Pilot decides next action.

---

## 6. Always-human paths — policy

Agents **may edit** the always-human paths when a feature requires. Writing SQL/yml/etc. is part of normal feature work.

**What they CANNOT do:**
- Push schema migrations to the live DB.
- Execute deploy scripts.
- `git push origin main`.
- Manually merge PRs (auto-merge.yml or Pilot merges).

**When PR touches always-human path:** auto-merge gate fails -> label removed -> architect or Pilot decides if to merge.

**Architect (orchestrator session) keeps authority** to run/approve always-human stuff (migrations, deploys). Same rule as today.

