## 7. Issue body workflow

T-file (`docs/tasks/<feat>/<task-slug>.md` committed) is **canonical source**. Paperclip Issue body is a short pointer (~15 lines):

```markdown
## Task: <short title>

Implement `docs/tasks/<feat>/<task-slug>.md`. Read T-file before any action.

## Branching
Base: `feat/<feat-slug>`. Create from `origin/dev` if doesn't exist.
Your branch: `task/<feat-slug>/<task-slug>`.
PR target: `feat/<feat-slug>` with label `auto-merge`.

## Worktree
`git worktree add /home/paperclip/worktrees/<issue-id> task/<feat-slug>/<task-slug>`
`cd /home/paperclip/worktrees/<issue-id>`

## When done
1. `git push origin task/<feat-slug>/<task-slug>`
2. `gh pr create --base feat/<feat-slug> --title "..." --body "..." --label auto-merge`
3. Comment URL on this Issue.

## If stuck
Comment on this Issue. Do NOT bypass.
```

Full Issue bodies live in `local/paperclip/tasks/<feat-slug>/issues.md` (gitignored) ready for API dispatch.

