## 8. Routine `review-pending-prs`

```bash
# Create Routine
curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{
    \"title\": \"Review unreviewed task/* PRs\",
    \"description\": \"cd /home/paperclip/repos/<your-repo>. Run 'gh pr list --state open --limit 30 --json ...' + jq filter to list pending PRs (--base with glob does NOT work). For each PR: read diff via 'gh pr diff', read T-file referenced in PR body, evaluate criteria in AGENTS.md. Comment APPROVE or REQUEST_CHANGES via 'gh pr comment'. Add label 'review-done' via 'gh pr edit --add-label review-done' after commenting. CRITICAL: if APPROVE, also re-apply 'auto-merge' label. If no pending PR, exit cleanly.\",
    \"assigneeAgentId\": \"<reviewer-id>\",
    \"priority\": \"medium\",
    \"concurrencyPolicy\": \"skip_if_active\",
    \"catchUpPolicy\": \"skip_missed\"
  }" \
  $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/companies/<co-id>/routines

# Cron trigger
curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "kind": "schedule",
    "cronExpression": "*/10 * * * *",
    "timezone": "America/Sao_Paulo",
    "enabled": true
  }' \
  $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/routines/<routine-id>/triggers
```

**A2 of the portable guide:** Paperclip does NOT connect to GitHub webhooks. Routine only fires periodic wakeup — reviewer itself scans PRs via `gh pr list` (instructed in AGENTS-reviewer.md).

