## 12. Anti-patterns relevant to your stack (from the portable guide)

The most applicable from the canonical Paperclip guide:

- **A1** — identical replicas don't parallelize. **Mitigation:** worktrees per-issue + explicit `assigneeAgentId` + schedule OFF default.
- **A2** — reviewer with no explicit trigger. **Mitigation:** Routine `review-pending-prs` + AGENTS-reviewer.md teaches scanning `gh pr list`.
- **A4** — Issue body without exit criterion. **Mitigation:** committed T-file has explicit criterion; Issue body just points at T-file.
- **A5** — agent doesn't run lint/typecheck locally. **Mitigation:** AGENTS-dev-primary.md requires lint + typecheck + test before each commit; fast-lane CI is fallback.
- **A6** — auto-merge without complete gate. **Mitigation:** gate B with 4 checks (CI + always-human + reviewer + coverage).
- **A9** — agents don't open PRs alone. **Mitigation:** `GITHUB_TOKEN` PAT + AGENTS.md has EXPLICIT end-of-task checklist with `gh pr create`.
- **A14** — agents invent columns that don't exist. **Mitigation:** AGENTS.md requires reading migrations directory before DB work.
- **A22** — shared CWD becomes race. **Mitigation:** mandatory worktrees per-issue (in AGENTS-dev-primary.md).

